IELTS Lesson 2
Warm Up: Discussion of current events and topics.
- Students create (1 minute) and ask (4 minutes in breakout groups) each other questions about home, friends
family, work, studies, interests. After they are to discuss the IELTS-Speaking-Student-Feedback Sheet
-So for task one, generate a list of questions on a topic, ex. leisure time in order of increasing difficulty.
-Listen to answers on a topic for example, spending time alone or with friends, work and life, the importance of
leisure time, and cultural questions.
Note:- for reluctant students to use good grammar encourage them to formulate a quick answer;
Teacher writes; What friend would you like to go on a holiday with? Your answer should start- “I’d like to go on
holiday with my friend (name)...” or the relative clause "The friend(s) I’d like to go on holiday with is/are...”

Speaking test
Read the Short Passage
Paradox of the choice is a concept regarding the overwhelming choices humans deal with today. By having too many
choices, people's expectations rise. That high expectation will result in a bitter disappointment, which ultimately causes
anxiety when trying to make a decision.
Paradox Of The Choice
Using The Main Points And Examples Describe Paradox Of The Choice.
Preparation Time: 30 seconds
Recording Time: 60 seconds
